House Resolution 776
By: Representatives Carter of the 93rd, Bennett of the 94th, and Hugley of the 141st
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Tisa Smart-Washington; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, March is celebrated as Women's History Month, a time to honor and recognize
3 the invaluable contributions of women throughout history and across all fields and trades;
4 and
5 WHEREAS,Tisa Smart-Washington 's contributions to the community reflect the core values
6 of Women's History Month; and
7 WHEREAS, Tisa is an accomplished public servant and trailblazing leader who has served
8 as Tax Commissioner of Rockdale County, Georgia, since 2016; and
9 WHEREAS, her journey in tax administration began in 2013, when she made history as the
10 first African American to be appointed Chief Deputy Tax Commissioner in Rockdale
11 County; and
12 WHEREAS, her 2016 election marked another milestone as she became the first African
13 American woman elected Tax Commissioner in the county, and she further cemented her
