14 legacy as the first African American and the first woman to serve more than one term in the
15 office; and
16 WHEREAS, in addition to her elected role, Tisa contributes her expertise at the state level,
17 currently serving as Communications Chair and District Leader for the Georgia Association
18 of Tax Officials and as Treasurer for the Tax Commissioners' Technology Development
19 Council of Georgia; and
20 WHEREAS, during her tenure as Chair of the Rockdale County Democratic Party, Tisa led
21 the charge in fielding a full slate of Democratic candidates in every local race-an
22 unprecedented move known as the "Slate of Eight"; and
23 WHEREAS, this groundbreaking effort resulted in the most significant political power shift
24 in Georgia during the 2012 election cycle and reshaped Rockdale County's political
25 landscape, opening doors for African American leadership and inspiring future generations
26 to step into public service; and
27 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding contributions of this
28 remarkable woman are recognized during Women's History Month.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body recognize and commend Tisa Smart-Washington for her
31 unwavering dedication to her community and extend sincere best wishes for her continued
32 health and happiness.
